  "texts": [
    "Taking a closer look at the average citation counts across different collaboration types, papers authored by individuals affiliated with private companies, exhibit lower citation rates, with an average of 16.88 citations per paper.",
    "In works published by US-linked authors only, the average number of citations was 31.95, and for EU-linked authors, this number dropped to 15.4, 52% less.",
    "In China's publications, this average plummets to 6.41 citations per paper.",
    "In collaborations between the regions, the US dropped its citations when collaborating with both, China and the EU, with 15.87 and 17.8 respectively.",
    "However, from China's and Europe's perspectives, the collaborations with the US increased their rates."
  ],
